<item>
            <title>[HIVE-108] sampling does not use internal column name </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-108</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sampling does not use internal column name, it uses column table name instead - which will not work in case there is any operator between table&lt;br/&gt;
scan and sampling, which is possible with column pruning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following test breaks: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(assuming srcbucket has more than 1 column: in this case 2 columns: key and value)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#8211; no input pruning, sample filter&lt;br/&gt;
EXPLAIN&lt;br/&gt;
SELECT s.key&lt;br/&gt;
FROM srcbucket TABLESAMPLE (BUCKET 1 OUT OF 5 on key) s;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SELECT s.key&lt;br/&gt;
FROM srcbucket TABLESAMPLE (BUCKET 1 OUT OF 5 on key) s;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
